description: UI and CSS conventions for mobile-first WC-Advisor screens
globs: frontend/src/**/*.{css,html}
alwaysApply: false
---

# UI/CSS Rules

- Build mobile-first layouts, then scale up with responsive breakpoints.
- Do not introduce external UI component libraries.
- Keep HTML semantic and accessible (labels, roles, and keyboard-friendly interactions).
- Prefer simple, reusable class patterns over deeply nested selectors.
- Maintain visual consistency with existing spacing, typography, and color tokens.

# UX Focus

- Prioritize map/list usability on small screens.
- Ensure detail sheets and filters remain clear and touch-friendly.
